rComments: I really enjoyed this professor's class. He was available outside of class time, responded to emails quickly and covered the course material well. I enjoyed Political Theory before this class and afterwards I loved it! Plus, to be honest, he is the archetypal hot professor, although I think he cut off his hair swoosh lol. Great class, great prof.
I believe there is a difference between having a topic approved and having a thesis approved.

Had him for modern political thought II.  Very good, in depth study of a few major thinkers.  Lectures very well, clear and knowledgeable.  Didn't have to do any of the readings, he only really covers lecture material on tests.  Bit of a hard marker for the essay.

Nice guy, good looking, well meaning. Myself being a pol science grad I needed 1 more elective so I took his class but my responses were too advanced for the course work (midterm & final) as he had stated. He slashed marks like crazy because of it? If you are 2nd + year pol science students do not take his class. Stick to classes at you're level.

Well he's a Seth Cohen clone, so that is helpful (haha) and his slides were interesting and amusing (as he's a goofball and likess to make them with crazy backgrounds). His lectures make the material more relatable and he's always cracking jokes which makes things fun. He gave an exact outline for the exam, which was great! overall he's a good prof
I loved this class! Professor Meynell has a fascinating take on Canadian politics, and I came away wanting to get involved.
Meynell is a great professor who really cares about his students. He was always available and happy to help, and I was truly inspired by several of his lectures. What more can you ask for?

He's is definitely someone who will captivate your attention, a really vivid personality but not  good at relaying information, I found a lot of it to be more throughly explained in the textbook...also I found it difficult to do well on his essay but the exams were straightforward...I had him at Waterloo!
Totally engaging prof who brought Canadian politics to life. I thought his use of on-line videos was totally  on topic and very effective.

Meynell has some serious Charm and Charisma. They arn't kidding about him trailing off though. We just watched a WSIB commercial with a girl is scalded in the face. I just wish I got to see the 'big hair'. His Midterms for this class are straightforward defintion and significance of term. Essay was handed back later then his purposed time though.

Had him at UW, he is very picky in his exam answers. Hes a good guy who means well, but his teaching methods are terrible, especially for those students without a politics background. Felt more like a 3rd/4th year course.
Meynell is dynamic and makes Canadian politics interesting. He is both relaxed and professional. I got a lot out of this course. By the way, I took his course at Waterloo

I had Meynell at UofW. Pretty cool guy, definitely knows his stuff and has done amazing things, but as a teacher he's so random. He'll trail off and never finish sentences. He skips over powerpoint notes. Clearly not a good prof for those without a solid background of polital science knowledge.
a lot of fun, knows his**** but not so great at teaching... he does use info web though
inspiring
No Comments
Ditto to the positive comments here.
Dr. Meynell is a great teacher with a lot to show his students. Accomplished professor with a great sense of humor. Used his microphone in interesting ways. He is also extremely good looking.
Great prof!

Well he's a Seth Cohen clone, so that is helpful (haha) and his slides were interesting and amusing (as he's a goofball and likess to make them with crazy backgrounds). His lectures make the material more relatable and he's always cracking jokes which makes things fun. He gave an exact outline for the exam, which was great! overall he's a good prof
good teacher kinda unclear

professor meynell is hot hot hot! i had a dream about him in which we went shopping and he bought vinyl pants..and he looked great.seriously though, he's very interesting, extremely passionate and a sharp dresser to boot. his assignments and exams are fair, so if you study you'll do well.does anyone know if he's single?

He was an okay prof, but its very hard not to like him. Kind of a goofball. He seemed prepared most of the time, but totally lacked control of the classroom (or was it that he didn't care?). He is helpful if you ask him, but there is quite a lot of reading.

The hardest prof I've had this term. He expects a lot of reading, almost like thinks he's the only class you have that term. Is prompt in answering questions, and very approachable. Extremely difficult in marking. Exams are really tough. expects perfect gammer. Doesn't give "a"'s
Professor Meynell was a great teacher and is very passionate about his work. I highly recommend this course.
I think he was very well prepared for class, with his powerpoint each week. Class went very well with readings. He also had office hours...but complained no one ever went.
He makes lectures actually enjoyable but the material can be difficult to comprehend with the laid back style... assignments are moderate
No Comments

Yes, his hairdo is mildly amusing. I really like his lecturing and I like how he doesn't accept b.s. answers from the crowd. I have yet to get an essay back, so can't comment on that, but he does have an excellent way of explaining the subject matter, I find.
I wouldn't piss on him if he was on fire in the desert.
Makes the subject matter interesting, but easily distracted.  Lectures seem unprepared.  A few Powerpoint slides might have helped him stay focused.

Provides little in the way of positive feedback. Is quick to tell you what you did wrong, but gives little insight as to what you did right on assignments. On the other hand, never indicates to anyone in class that they are completely off the mark with what they said.
Difficult prof.  Study hard and don't slack on essay's

i agree with the above said comments I wish i knew before how picky, tough and full of detail he would be. he is an entertaing teacher, a very nice guy (deeply animated) but expects a lot from a compressed summer FIRST year course.  it has a lot of information and is intersting.... but he warned hes a hard marker.

He quickly fell behind on the lectures and never seemed prepared. Could not uphold his commitments to get assignments back resulting in the final essay being due after the end of the semester. Seems like an okay guy personally, and his giant hairdue is mildly amusing.

he's funny in a cartoonish way, but I doubt that he prepared for a single lecture. He's so unorganized that our final paper is due after our semester is over.  How crazy is that? He also gave me a C ( my lowest mark ever) for a paper he called "very well writen".  Huh?
